@startuml 2NAuthenticationFlow
title "2N MV SDK: Partner Integration Flow"
 
participant "Configure Pro?\nCompany" as PartnerAdmin
participant "Crestron Home Platform" as PartnerBackend
participant "2N API" as API
participant my2N
participant User
participant "Crestron Mobile App" as PartnerApp
participant "2N MV MSDK" as SDK 
participant "2N Intercom" as Intercom
 
== 1. One-time Configure Pro setup: Intercom ==
note over PartnerAdmin: Detect 2N Intercoms
 
PartnerAdmin->API: POST Create Device (Intercom)\n(Site ID, serial number)
API-->PartnerAdmin: Device ID (Intercom)
 
note over my2N: Intercom registered in site
 
== 2. Provisioning: Shadow User + Device (App) ==

PartnerAdmin->PartnerBackend: Settings\n (enable push notifications for intercom doorbell)

note over PartnerBackend: New user wants 2N calling for door station
 
PartnerBackend->API: POST Create Shadow User + Device (App)\n(Site ID)
API-->PartnerBackend: {Shadow User ID, Device ID (App)}
 
note over PartnerBackend: Store mapping:\nPartner User ↔ Shadow User ID
 
note over my2N: Shadow User created\nDevice (App) created\nShadow User assigned to Device (App)
 
== 3a. Runtime: Login ==
 
User->PartnerApp: Opens app, logs in\nPartner credentials



== 3. Runtime: Login ==
 
User->PartnerApp: Opens app, logs in\nPartner credentials
PartnerApp->PartnerBackend: Authenticate
PartnerBackend-->PartnerApp: Auth OK
 
PartnerBackend->API: GET Access Token\n(Shadow User ID)
API-->PartnerBackend: Access Token (valid for X hours)
 
PartnerBackend-->PartnerApp: 2N Access Token
 
PartnerApp->SDK: login(accessToken)
SDK-->PartnerApp: Login OK, SDK ready
 
== 4. Calling ==
 
User->PartnerApp: Taps Push Notification
PartnerApp->SDK: call(deviceId)
SDK->Intercom: Initiate call
Intercom-->SDK: Call connected
SDK-->PartnerApp: Call connected callback

note over PartnerApp: Audio & Video \nstreams established

== 5. Token Refresh ==
 
note over SDK: Token expired / nearing expiration
 
SDK-->PartnerApp: Token expired callback
PartnerApp->PartnerBackend: Request new 2N token
PartnerBackend->API: GET Access Token\n(Shadow User ID)
API-->PartnerBackend: New Access Token
PartnerBackend-->PartnerApp: New Access Token
 
PartnerApp->SDK: refreshToken(newAccessToken)
SDK-->PartnerApp: Token refreshed, SDK ready